	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_1_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a blessing from the spirits!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_2_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} enforces the ancient trials of manhood, sending boys out onto the savannah to prove their strength.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_3_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} calls all able-bodied men to war!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_4_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} focuses his efforts into promoting the traditional way of life.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_5_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} discovers the illegal City State mining of [ICON_RES_GOLD] and [ICON_RES_GEMS]!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_6_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ZULU_UE_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} begins a process of peace and reconciliation in Zululand.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>Many More Hills To Climb</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP">
			<Text>Sawubona, Warchief. Ancestors guide you. The Sangomas have returned from their sacred places with the meaning of your dream.[NEWLINE]Come Shaka, hear the will of the spirits.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Receive a Great Person of your choice.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>Utilise {1_YieldCost} to encourage a return to the Plains. Cities gain +1 [ICON_FOOD] Food and +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production for every 3 Plains Tiles within workable range.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Workers leave the poor arable land to join the Mfecane. {2_InstantYield} becomes an Impi in every City, and Farms yield -1 [ICON_FOOD] Food for {4_Turns}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Send {1_YieldCost} to support our rural communities. Villages produce +1 [ICON_FOOD] Food and +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production, and you receive 2 copies of [ICON_RES_TEA] Tea.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>You sieze a copy of [ICON_RES_GEMS] Gems and a copy of [ICON_RES_GOLD] Gold. The spread of so much illegal material increases [ICON_STRENGTH] Crime thresholds by 10%.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_HELP_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>The coming together reduces [ICON_CULTURE] Boredom thresholds by -10%, and each City builds a Church.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>*There is a child, born under the blessings of all the ancestors. They have the power to both destroy and heal*[NEWLINE]We will seek out this child with the second sight. They will aid us.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*The spirits are restless. Too many Zulu dwell idle in the Cities, away from the open plains*[NEWLINE]It is clear. We have strayed from our heritage. We must bring back the old rites of passage, of feats of strength upon the savannah.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*This war will be unlike any other. If any Zulu dreamt of bringing honour to his ancestors, it is now, in this great conflict*[NEWLINE]Send the messangers from the greatest Palace to the smallest Farmstead. All men are called to war!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*Your ancestors are pleased with the honour you have shown in your leadership, but there is still more to be done. You must look to the Villages*[NEWLINE]We shall continue to settle the plains, and live the old ways. Each Sangoma will take back the Gold of our conquests, to build anew.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>*There is no doubt your enemies have proven themselves duplicitous and cowardly, but the true horror is hidden below, where they defile the Earth*[NEWLINE]It is good that the spirits alerted us to this. Slaves mining for their masters' greed is truely evil.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ZULU_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>*Many wars. Many peoples. All their ancestors weeping over their collective pain. It is time to heal*[NEWLINE]Let us come together as one people, one family, irrespective of colour or creed. In Zululand, we are one.</Text>
		</Row>

		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_ZULU_UE_DUMMY">
			<Text></Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
</GameData>